SUMMARY:Reimagining Heat Information in Toronto - by Toronto Climate
  Observatory
LOCATION:CSI Spadina
DESCRIPTION:More info:
  https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSerjcZFPiLhuLJfYCVR-qD3NKAw_za5F
 w2y89N3Jtz6knvbXg/viewform?pli=1\n\nHosted by Toronto Climate Observatory
  (https://www.climateobservatory.ca/)\n\nWhen heat waves hit Toronto\, who
  gets warned? Whose knowledge counts? And why do heat alerts so often fail
  to reach the people who need them most? Current heat maps and warning
  systems are typically designed by institutions—not by the communities
  living through extreme heat. This workshop flips that script.
END:VEVENT
